Everything I ate at Disney while wearing a white shirt. I thought wearing a light colored shirt would help fight the heat, but keeping it clean was another battle in itself. Here’s a list of what I ate

1. Cookie Croissant @ Maurice’s Treats - 8/10
Crunchy and large. Very nostalgic and had an elevated butter cookie from the tin vibe.

2. Cold Brew Black Caf @ Docking Bay 7 Food and Cargo - 9/10
The toppings were the star, sweet cream cheese and chocolate puffs. Great way to recharge for the day and love the texture from the puffs. Fun!

3. Boysen Apple Freeze @ Maurice’s Treats - 7/10
Tasted like a slushy apple sauce. A little on the sweet side but very refreshing 

4. Garlic Cheesy Pretzel Bread @ Edelweiss Snacks - 10/10
A must get!!!!! Love the cheesy garlic gooeyness at the center. Bread is good on its own but even better with the marinara sauce. 

5. Flos Famous Fried Chicken @ Flo’s V8 Cafe - 10/10
Chicken was juicy, crunchy and not heavily battered and flavorful. The mash was fantastic! Similar to PLAZA inn. 

6. QuesaBirria @ Cocina Cucamonga Mexican Grill - 10/10
I was shocked how good this was, especially for a theme park. There was so much meat and the ratio  of the cheese was spot on. The corn tortilla was perfectly crunchy and it was not super salty. If it was topped with raw onions it would have been 12/10. 

Shirt is from H&M Oversized Fit size Medium 
Hat is from Disneyland

Enjoying family time with some food from Panini Kabob Grill. It’s been a while since I’ve seen my family so it was great to see everyone. We ordered three family combos. Each combo feed 4-6 people.  The original combo comes with a tray of rice, a tray of salad and 4 large chicken skewers with veggies for $70.

We altered the order by upgrading the meats. 

1st Original Family combo
Rice, avocado salad and CHICKEN kabobs

2nd Upgraded Family combo
Rice, Mediterranean salad and BEEF KOOBIDEH Kabobs

3rd Upgraded Family combo
Rice, Caesar salad and 1/2 CHICKEN 1/2 SALMON kabobs

Added 16oz hummus and 16oz tzatziki

Food prepping because I have guests coming over for the weekend. This way I can spend more quality time with them. Here are some of my tips and hacks. 

Washing fruits and veggies. 
- rinse the produce first
- submerge them in a bowl of cool water 
- add baking soda 
- massage / stir produce and make sure baking soda is dissolved into water
- rinse then air dry and store

Frozen Garlic cubes
- mince garlic cloves in food processor 
- scoop minced garlic into ziplock bags
- Remove air and flatten bags so minced garlic lays flat. 
-score cubes with chopsticks 
- lay on baking sheet and freeze

Watermelon 
- wash exterior 
- cut watermelon in half
- cut off rhine
- cut horizontally across watermelon half
- cut vertically from top of watermelon to bottom so they end up in cubes. Make sure you support the side of the watermelon so it retains its shape.
- find a large bowl and cup it over the watermelon 
- flip it with cutting board and it’s ready to serve.
